Description: Fast, scalable linkage disequilibrium (LD) block detection for
    genome-wide SNP data. Supports two LD metrics: standard r^2 (fast, suitable
    for 10M+ markers) and the kinship-adjusted rV^2 (Mangin et al. 2012,
    Heredity 108(3):285-291) for structured or related populations.
    The clique-based segmentation algorithm is from Kim et al. (2018,
    Bioinformatics 34(4):588-596).
    The clique-based Big-LD segmentation algorithm is accelerated throughout
    by Rcpp/RcppArmadillo and OpenMP. A unified multi-format I/O layer reads
    numeric dosage CSV, HapMap, VCF, SeqArray GDS, and PLINK BED files.
    Downstream modules cover: haplotype phasing (statistical via Beagle,
    pedigree-based transmission, or pre-phased VCF); haplotype extraction
    for phased and unphased data; diversity metrics (richness, expected
    heterozygosity, Shannon entropy); post-GWAS QTL region definition with
    pleiotropic block detection; haplotype feature matrices for genomic
    prediction (additive 0/1/2 or presence/absence 0/2 encoding); and
    output writers for numeric CSV, HapMap, and diversity CSV formats
    compatible with TASSEL, GAPIT, rrBLUP, BGLR, and ASReml-R.
    Automatic parameter tuning against GWAS marker coverage is also provided.
